Description: Corroded iron wedge or short chisel, with rectangular cross-section; convex sides tapering to the tip with a flattened head at the opposite end.
Curator's comments: One of the "chisels (pl. xxxviii. 15 to 20), of which about forty were kept, beside many rejected", mentioned by Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 78 § 78, p. 110, pl. xxxviii, 15.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 78 § 78, p. 110, pl. xxxviii, 15)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.47, p.75, p.184, pl.26)
Condition: Heavily corroded and incomplete (one side broken away)
